                            THE HOUSE COMMITTEE ON
                         STANDARDS OF OFFICIAL CONDUCT



   The House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct (often referred
   to as just "The Ethics Committee") is charged with reviewing all
   ethics complaints filed against members of Congress. The committee
   does not provide documentation to the public about ongoing inquiries
   or investigations (which is okay - we do). Still, you can reach the
   committee and its staff at:


          The House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct

          Room HT2, Capitol Building

          Washington, DC 20515


          Phone number: (202) 225-7103

   The composition of the House Ethics Committee is unusual in that it's
   evenly divided, with five Republicans and five Democrats. If
   you'd like to comment to committee members regarding the cases against
   Newt, they can be reached at the addresses and phone numbers below. If
   your representative sits on the committee, even better.

   Incidentally, only one of the committee members (Maryland Democrat
   Ben Cardin) has an e-mail address (so if you're an angry pro-Newt
   flamer, at least be cool enough to thank him for providing e-mail
   access for his on-line constituents).


